Phase 1 — Measure First

Before changing code:

flutter run --profile

Then enable:

showPerformanceOverlay: true

Check:

UI Thread (Build)
Raster Thread (Render)

If either spikes above:

16ms = 60 FPS
8ms = 120 FPS

you'll see jank.

Phase 2 — Fix Chat Screen (Highest Priority)
Use ListView.builder

❌ Bad

Column(
children: messages.map(...).toList(),
)

✅ Good

ListView.builder(
itemCount: messages.length,
itemBuilder: (context,index){
return MessageBubble(...);
},
)
Add Keys
MessageBubble(
key: ValueKey(message.id),
)

This helps Flutter reuse widgets.

Use const Widgets

❌

Text("Online")

✅

const Text("Online")

Apply everywhere possible.

Separate Message Bubble Widget

Don't build the bubble directly inside ListView.

ChatScreen
├─ MessageList
├─ MessageBubble
├─ InputBar

Each widget becomes smaller and rebuilds less.

Phase 3 — Fix Keyboard Jank

Most chat apps use:

Scaffold(
resizeToAvoidBottomInset: false,
)

Then manually handle keyboard.

Example:

AnimatedPadding(
duration: Duration(milliseconds: 250),
padding: EdgeInsets.only(
bottom: MediaQuery.of(context).viewInsets.bottom,
),
child: MessageInput(),
)

Benefits:

Less layout recalculation
Smoother keyboard animation
Reverse Message List

Messenger and WhatsApp style:

ListView.builder(
reverse: true,
)

This improves scrolling performance for chat apps.

Phase 4 — Image Optimization

Install:

cached_network_image:

Replace:

Image.network(url)

with

CachedNetworkImage(
imageUrl: url,
)

For:

Avatars
Story images
Profile photos
Group images

This alone can remove lots of scroll lag.

Phase 5 — Riverpod Optimization
Bad
Widget build() {
final state = ref.watch(chatProvider);

return Scaffold(...);
}

Entire screen rebuilds.

Better
Consumer(
builder: (_, ref, __) {
final messages = ref.watch(chatProvider);

return MessageList(messages);
},
)

Only MessageList rebuilds.

Best
ref.watch(
chatProvider.select(
(state) => state.messages,
),
);

Only rebuild when messages change.

Phase 6 — Local Database Optimization

If using Isar:

final messages = await isar.messages
    .where()
    .chatIdEqualTo(chatId)
    .findAll();

Add indexes.

Example:

@Index()
String chatId;
@Index()
DateTime createdAt;

Without indexes:

10000 messages
↓
slow query

With indexes:

10000 messages
↓
fast query
Phase 7 — API Optimization

Use Dio Singleton.

class ApiClient {
static final Dio dio = Dio();
}

Never create Dio repeatedly.

❌

Dio dio = Dio();

inside every API call.

Phase 8 — Background Message Sync

Don't rebuild chat list every message.

Bad:

New Message
↓
Reload Entire Chat List

Good:

New Message
↓
Update Only Changed Chat

Example:

conversation.lastMessage = newMessage;

instead of re-fetching everything.

Phase 9 — Navigation Optimization

For chat apps:

Home
Chat
Profile
Settings

Use:

IndexedStack

instead of recreating screens.

IndexedStack(
index: currentTab,
children: [...]
)

This is what Messenger-like apps do.